#: _guides/security-openid-connect-providers.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Depending on your developer API subscription level, some providers may enforce a rather strict request rate limiting policy."
msgstr "根据您的开发人员 API 订阅级别，某些提供商可能会执行相当严格的请求速率限制政策。"

#: _guides/security-openid-connect-providers.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "It may not be a problem when Quarkus fetches public verification keys from OIDC-compliant providers like the <<google>> provider and keeps verifying the user session with these keys locally. However, for pure OAuth2 providers where only an access token is available and which has to be verified indirectly by requesting UserInfo from the provider endpoint on every request done by an already authenticated user, it can become a problem."
msgstr "当 Quarkus 从符合 OIDC 标准的提供商（如 <<google>> 提供商）获取公共验证密钥，并在本地使用这些密钥不断验证用户会话时，这可能不是问题。但是，对于只有访问令牌的纯 OAuth2 提供商来说，必须在已通过身份验证的用户每次请求时通过请求提供商端点的 UserInfo 来间接验证访问令牌，这可能会成为一个问题。"

#: _guides/security-openid-connect-providers.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Therefore, UserInfo is embedded in an internally generated ID token and is encrypted in the session cookie. You can disable it with `quarkus.oidc.cache-user-info-in-idtoken=false`."
msgstr "因此，UserInfo 嵌入到内部生成的 ID 标记中，并在会话 cookie 中加密。您可以通过 `quarkus.oidc.cache-user-info-in-idtoken=false` 禁用它。"

#: _guides/security-openid-connect-providers.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Alternatively, use a default or custom UserInfo cache provider, please see the xref:security-oidc-bearer-token-authentication#token-introspection-userinfo-cache[Token Introspection and UserInfo cache] section of the \"OpenID Connect (OIDC) Bearer token authentication\" guide."
msgstr "或者，使用默认或自定义的用户信息缓存提供程序，请参阅 \"OpenID Connect (OIDC) Bearer token authentication \"指南中的 xref:security-oidc-bearer-token-authentication.adoc#token-introspection-userinfo-cache[令牌自省和用户信息缓存] 部分。"

